    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as the undisputed cornerstone of the lineup. With a score of 74.65, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a 14% platoon edge against P. Lambert, cementing his status as the highest-ceiling play today. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.02) and **Jacob Wilson** (69.81) represent the next tier of reliability. **Jacob Wilson** is particularly intriguing, as the combination of a high park factor and a favorable projection against Noah Cameron creates a high-leverage opportunity, even with a pending lineup status. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** rounds out our top-tier hitters, utilizing a strong 14% dynamic platoon advantage to overcome a neutral matchup against F. Peralta and secure a score of 60.56.\n\nOur primary lineup decisions for the middle infield were dictated by the specific need for speed to keep pace in stolen bases. **Nasim Nunez** (47.72) receives a slight bump due to F. Peralta\u2019s slow delivery, which boosts our potential for stolen bases, keeping him in the mix despite a lower base projection. The most difficult decision involved **Coby Mayo** (40.70), who barely makes the cut. While he faces a challenging matchup against P. Lambert, his park factor provides enough of a cushion to stay in the lineup over our other reserves. We remain cautious with **Drake Baldwin** (54.14) and **Heliot Ramos** (48.04), both of whom are facing difficult left-handed pitchers; their scores are tethered to their high lineup spots, which provide essential volume, though they carry heightened risk due to the opposing SP skill.\n\nThe bench remains stagnant due to schedule quirks, with **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill** all seeing their production locked at zero due to team off-days. We are continuing to monitor **Luis Robert Jr.** on the IL, as his absence\u2014along with the rest of our depth like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Brady House**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks**\u2014remains a concern for our overall roster depth. Today\u2019s success hinges on **Gunnar Henderson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** capitalizing on their favorable matchups to carry the offensive load while we navigate the marginal efficiency of our bottom-of-the-order hitters.",
